spans.text: His gore-died lips , which on the clottered locks Of the half-devoured head he wiped , and thus Began : ' Wouldst thou revive the deep despair
who thou art nor on what errand Sent hither
me Count Ugolino , and Ruggieri , Pisa's perfidious prelate , this
me Count Ugolino , and Ruggieri , Pisa's perfidious prelate , this
say if he have injured me
a sleep Prophetic of my woes with direful hand
methought Towards Pisa's mount , that intercepts the view Of Lucca , chased by hellhounds gaunt and bloody A wolf fullgrown
hellhounds gaunt and bloody A wolf fullgrown
fleet and equal speed His young ones
the chase : the panting sire , Of strength bereft , his helpless offspring soon Overtaken beheld , and in their trembling flanks The hungry pack their sharp-set fangs embrued
the fears of sleep , and now the hour Of timely food
the dreadful clank of bars And fastening bolts
my children's eyes Speechless my sight
These miserable limbs with flesh you clothed
These miserable limbs with flesh you clothed
three before my eyes Died one by one
before my eyes Died one by one
